The paper deals with impartial selection, a problem in the field of game theory (cs.GT) and graph algorithms (cs.DS). The proposed mechanisms are randomized algorithms, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The problem of impartial selection also has applications in social networks and voting systems, which fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
